v>
      </div>

     =20
      <div class=3D"comment-content">

        <p>Just to clarify that the specificity calculator isn=E2=80=99t en=
tirely accurate. For example, if you had an element with 11 classes applied=
 to it, it would not outrank an element with a single ID selector. </p>
<p>for example,</p>
<p>.a .b .c .d .e .f .g .h .i .j a.k { color:red; }<br>
#myel {color:blue;}</p>
<p>&lt;span class=3D=E2=80=9Da b c d e f g h i j k=E2=80=9D id=3D=E2=80=9Dm=
yel=E2=80=9D&gt;would still be blue.&lt;/span&gt;</p>
<p>The chances of this are slim but important to note.</p>
<div class=3D"explanation">Authors note: this is one of the reasons this ar=
ticle was updated.</div>

      </div>

      <div class=3D"comment-actions">
        <div class=3D"reply">
