<p>That=E2=80=99s why a separated notation (commas are most common) is pref=
erred when writing specificity values.  See <a href=3D"http://meyerweb.com/=
eric/css/link-specificity.html" rel=3D"nofollow ugc">http://meyerweb.com/er=
ic/css/link-specificity.html</a> for an example, or <a href=3D"http://www.w=
3.org/TR/CSS21/cascade.html#specificity" rel=3D"nofollow ugc">the CSS2.1 sp=
ecification itself</a>.</p>
<div class=3D"explanation">Authors note: another reason this article was up=
dated=E2=80=A6</div>

