v>
      </div>

     =20
      <div class=3D"comment-content">

        <p>I=E2=80=99m aware this post is old, but wanted to add useful inf=
ormation encase someone else read this comment in the future.</p>
<p><a href=3D"http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS2/cascade.html" title=3D"Assigning pr=
operty values, Cascading, and Inheritance" rel=3D"nofollow ugc">http://www.=
w3.org/TR/CSS2/cascade.html</a></p>
<p><strong>6.4.2 !important rules</strong></p>
<blockquote><p>
  CSS attempts to create a balance of power between author and user style s=
heets. By default, rules in an author=E2=80=99s style sheet override those =
in a user=E2=80=99s style sheet (see cascade rule 3).
</p></blockquote>

