mment-time"><a href=3D"https://css-tricks.com/specifics-on-css-specificity/=
#comment-714558"><span class=3D"screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#=
</a> <time datetime=3D"2013-11-26T17:32:14-08:00">November 26, 2013</time><=
/div>
      </div>

     =20
      <div class=3D"comment-content">

        <p>I found your =E2=80=9C!important=E2=80=9D on specificity explana=
tion little confusing. For example:</p>
<pre><code>&lt;style&gt;
    .foo{ color:red!important;}
    a {color:green;}
&lt;/style&gt;

&lt;p class=3D"foo"&gt;
       &lt;a href=3D"#"&gt;Foo&lt;/a&gt; Bar
&lt;/p&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>The color of =E2=80=9CFoo=E2=80=9D text in =E2=80=9Ca=E2=80=9D will be g=
reen but most people might think it is red.</p>

      </div>

      <div class=3D"comment-actions">
        <div class=3D"reply">
                  </div>
      </div>

    </div>

