  <li class=3D"comment even depth-2" id=3D"li-comment-760030">

    <div class=3D"comment-wrap" id=3D"comment-760030">

      <div class=3D"comment-author-wrap">
        <div class=3D"comment-author">Dylan Archer</div> <div class=3D"comm=
ent-time"><a href=3D"https://css-tricks.com/specifics-on-css-specificity/#c=
omment-760030"><span class=3D"screen-reader">Permalink to comment</span>#</=
a> <time datetime=3D"2013-12-04T18:31:54-08:00">December 4, 2013</time></di=
v>
      </div>

     =20
      <div class=3D"comment-content">

        <p><code>!important</code> applies to the element it is assigned to=
, not child elements. I believe <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> is considered a chil=
d of <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> in this case. Any text within the parent elemen=
t would be red regardless of what styles were applied to the universal <cod=
e>p</code> selecter; However <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> would retain it=E2=80=
=99s specified styles.</p>

      </div>

      <div class=3D"comment-actions">
        <div class=3D"reply">
                  </div>
      </div>

    </div>

   =20
