    <div class=3D"comment-wrap" id=3D"comment-1411475">

      <div class=3D"comment-author-wrap">
        <div class=3D"comment-author">Will Murray (Willscrlt)</div> <div cl=
ass=3D"comment-time"><a href=3D"https://css-tricks.com/specifics-on-css-spe=
cificity/#comment-1411475"><span class=3D"screen-reader">Permalink to comme=
nt</span>#</a> <time datetime=3D"2014-03-21T20:12:39-07:00">March 21, 2014<=
/time></div>
      </div>

     =20
      <div class=3D"comment-content">

        <p>I found the issue. There is a @media selector above that covered=
 the style I was trying to override. Therefore, I suppose that means that @=
media has a very high value, though I=E2=80=99m not exactly sure where it w=
ould fall into this hierarchy. Perhaps that information could be added to t=
his article?</p>

      </div>

      <div class=3D"comment-actions">
        <div class=3D"reply">
